pull_request.title: Fix: Comprehensive Bug Hunt and UX/Accessibility Improvements
pull_request.body:
This commit addresses a wide range of issues identified during a comprehensive QA assessment of the web application. The fixes improve functionality, accessibility, user experience, and visual integrity.

Key changes include:
- **Critical Bug Fixes:**
  - Replaced all broken or non-direct image links with high-quality, functional URLs.
  - Made the "Location" buttons functional by linking them to Google Maps searches.
  - Implemented a placeholder "feature coming soon" alert for the "Add to Itinerary" button to manage user expectations.

- **Accessibility Enhancements:**
  - Made all attraction cards keyboard-focusable and operable via "Enter" or "Space" keys.
  - Implemented robust focus management for the sanctuary view, ensuring focus is correctly trapped and returned upon closing.
  - Added appropriate `role` and `aria-label` attributes to interactive elements.

- **UX and Performance Improvements:**
  - Replaced the misleading "clock" icon with a "plus" icon for the "Add to Itinerary" button.
  - Added a data URI poster to the landing video to prevent 404 errors and improve loading experience.
  - Added comments to `index.html` recommending image optimization for production environments.

These changes result in a more robust, accessible, and user-friendly application.
